section.t:
    The Content-ID header field included in the header fields of a SIP message
    identifies a body part consisting of the message-body of the SIP message, and
    the metadata provided by:


        the Content-ID header field itself;

        a MIME-Version header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message;

        a Content-Disposition header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message;

        a Content-Encoding header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message;

        a Content-Language header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message;

        a Content-Length header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message; and

        a Content-Type header field, if included in the header fields of
the SIP message.
